Doc,<br><br>
In this instance I totally agree.  There are means and organizations which offer the less advantaged aid.  Veterans  can get this help.  I have witnessed the scam artists so many times it does cloud my vision to those who may need my help.<br><br>
I like you have a problem with their behavior.  I know many of my friends who have made offers of jobs and the old I'll feed you for work.  Only in one instance did this meet with anything, but a direct insult.  Just try giving one too little.  I offered to bring one into a restaurant and feed him.  No way.<br><br>
I saw a Sioux once huddled in the ceppar access of a public building next to a vent.  Temp -25 F.  When asked what he needed, he asked to be allowed to stand by the exhaust.  He asked for nothing more, but the eyes told everything.  Proud and in pain.  In this instance you offer without thought.  There is always something in the eyes that talks.  You just don't see it in &quot;ramp bums&quot;.<br><br>
We used to call them panhandlers.  Hobos had a code and liked what they were.  The Bums were usually alkies.  I watched my father support those to no avail.<br><br>
Sorry, but we need a better way.
